---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro'; import PageHero from '../components/PageHero.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Applications — Leicester Space Week brand"><PageHero eyebrow="Applications" title="Built to travel." intro="The system is intentionally modular: enough consistency to be recognisable, enough flexibility to work for every contributor and context." /><section class="section"><div class="shell"><div class="cards"><article class="card"><span class="glyph">01</span><div><h3>Digital</h3><p>Use Navy-led compositions, high contrast type and a single amber action. Start with generous margins, then layer in one subtle orbit.</p></div></article><article class="card"><span class="glyph">02</span><div><h3>Social</h3><p>Use the icon mark for avatars. Event posts lead with a concise title, date and category; preserve clear space around partner marks.</p></div></article><article class="card"><span class="glyph">03</span><div><h3>Physical space</h3><p>On signage, banners and wayfinding, use large fields of Navy and short messages. The skyline can establish a location at scale.</p></div></article></div></div></section><section class="section" style="background:#e5e1d7"><div class="shell"><div class="section-head"><p class="eyebrow">Partner toolkit</p><h2>Share the stage.</h2><p>Partner logos are important, but the Leicester Space Week crest should retain clear recognition in event-owned communications.</p></div><div class="type-stage"><p class="eyebrow">Co-branding principle</p><p class="specimen" style="font-size:clamp(2.8rem,6vw,6rem)">LSW&nbsp;&nbsp;+&nbsp;&nbsp;Partner</p><div class="type-info"><div><h3>Equal clear space</h3><p>Separate marks with a thin vertical rule or a generous fixed gap. Align optical centres.</p></div><div><h3>Event first</h3><p>Where Leicester Space Week is the host, its mark appears first and is never smaller than the partner logo.</p></div></div></div></div></section></BaseLayout>
